    "E.W. Bullinger": "All will be \"new.\" The word rendered \"new\" ((...), kainos) means new, not merely as to\ntime, but as to kind and as to quality.\nThe heaven will be \"new\"; the earth \"new\"; for there will be \"no more curse,\" and therefore\nno more sin, or suffering, or sorrow.\nAmong these new things will be\na. xxi.\nv. 14-21.\n224\nft183 --  \u00b5yhlah ynpl bwj \u201cbonus coram Deo\u201d, Pagninus, Mercerus,\nDrusius, Amama, Rambachius; \u201cqui bonus videtur coram Deo ipso\u201d,\nJunius & Tremellius.\nft184 --  \u201cVir bonus et sapiens, qualem vix reperit unum, millibus e multio\nhominum, consultus Apollo.\u201d Auson. Idyll. 16."
